# Agent dev-team — check the board for `todo` issues on a schedule (flock-guarded).
# Install with:  crontab -e   (then paste a line below)
#
# Every minute (the script's flock makes overlapping ticks safe — a long-running
# issue simply holds the lock until it finishes):
* * * * * /bin/bash /srv/agent-team/scripts/issue-loop.sh >> /var/log/agent-team/cron.log 2>&1

# Or every 15 minutes:
# */15 * * * * /bin/bash /srv/agent-team/scripts/issue-loop.sh >> /var/log/agent-team/cron.log 2>&1

# Prerequisites:
#   mkdir -p /var/log/agent-team
#   scripts/.env present (chmod 600) with GITLAB_GROUP, GITLAB_TOKEN, TELEGRAM_TOKEN,
#   TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID — cron has a minimal environment, so the script sources scripts/.env
#   itself. Ensure `claude`, `node`, `git`, `jq`, `flock`, `curl` are on the cron PATH
#   (set PATH=... at the top of the crontab if needed).
